<paragraph blockId="23.[151,912,723,779]" box="[151,631,723,748]" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">
<heading box="[151,631,723,748]" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="23" pageNumber="252" reason="2">
<taxonomicName authority="Sueur &amp; Puissant, 2007" authorityName="Sueur &amp; Puissant" authorityYear="2007" box="[151,631,723,748]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicadetta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cantilatrix">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,376,724,748]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">Cicadetta cantilatrix</emphasis>
Sueur &amp;Puissant, 2007
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,912,723,779]" box="[227,912,755,779]" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">
German common name: Honigader-Bergzikade (
<bibRefCitation author="HERTACH, T." box="[750,905,755,779]" pageId="23" pageNumber="252" refId="ref17089" refString="HERTACH, T. 2010. Pechader-Bergzikade (Cicadetta montana) (p. 183). In: I NEICHEN, S. &amp; RUCKSTUHL, M. (eds). Stadtfauna - 600 Tierarten der Stadt Zurich. Haupt Verlag Bern, Stuttgart, Wien, 446 pp." type="book" year="2010">Hertach, 2010</bibRefCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="252" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1073,798,886]" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sueur &amp; Puissant" authorityYear="2007" box="[227,451,798,822]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicadetta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cantilatrix">
<emphasis box="[227,451,798,822]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">Cicadetta cantilatrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can often be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1772" box="[820,947,799,822]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicadetta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis box="[820,947,799,822]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">C. montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[957,1017,798,822]" pageId="23" pageNumber="252" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by a yellow to brown colouration of the basal venation of the fore wing (“Honigader” = honey coloured venation).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[151,392,913,937]" pageId="23" pageNumber="252" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1074,913,1545]" box="[151,392,913,937]" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">DISTRIBUTION (Fig. 9)</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="252" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1074,913,1545]" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sueur &amp; Puissant" authorityYear="2007" box="[227,366,945,969]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicadetta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cantilatrix">
<emphasis box="[227,366,945,969]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">C. cantilatrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described very recently and separated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Puissant &amp; Boulard" authorityYear="2000" box="[879,1041,945,969]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicadetta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerdaniensis">
<emphasis box="[879,1041,945,969]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">C. cerdaniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by acoustic characters (Sueur &amp; Puissant, 2007a). For the acoustic description Sueur &amp; Puissant integrated recordings from 
<collectingCountry box="[539,664,1009,1033]" name="Switzerland" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
(Martigny-Combe, VS), but the 
<typeStatus pageId="23" pageNumber="252">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus box="[248,338,1041,1065]" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">paratype</typeStatus>
were collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[532,607,1041,1065]" name="France" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">France</collectingCountry>
. The taxon has been discussed critically due to intermediary song patterns observed several times in northern 
<collectingCountry box="[842,967,1073,1097]" name="Switzerland" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="HERTACH, T." pageId="23" pageNumber="252" pagination="37 - 61" refId="ref17011" refString="HERTACH, T. 2007. Three species instead of only one: Distribution and ecology of the Cicadetta montana species complex (Hemiptera: Cicadoidea) in Switzerland. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft 80: 37 - 61." type="journal article" year="2007">Hertach, 2007</bibRefCitation>
). These intermediary song patterns are now interpreted as courtship songs of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sueur &amp; Puissant" authorityYear="2007" box="[151,294,1137,1161]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicadetta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cantilatrix">
<emphasis box="[151,294,1137,1161]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">C. cantilatrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="TRILAR, T. &amp; OGALA, M. &amp; ZWEDO, J." box="[311,503,1137,1161]" pageId="23" pageNumber="252" pagination="313 - 320" refId="ref19602" refString="TRILAR, T., G OGALA, M. &amp; S ZWEDO, J. 2006. Pyrenean Mountain Cicada Cicadetta cerdaniensis Puissant &amp; Boulard (Hemiptera: Cicadomorpha: Cicadidae) found in Poland. Polskie Pismo Entomologiczne 75 (2): 313 - 320." type="journal article" year="2006">
Trilar 
<emphasis box="[382,438,1137,1161]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">et al.</emphasis>
,2006
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="HERTACH, T." box="[517,670,1137,1161]" pageId="23" pageNumber="252" pagination="25 - 40" refId="ref17141" refString="HERTACH, T. 2011. Spectacular song pattern from the Sicilian Mountains: The new cicada species Cicadetta anapaistica sp. n. (Hemiptera: Cicadidae). Zootaxa 2771: 25 - 40." type="journal article" year="2011">Hertach, 2011</bibRefCitation>
) which are very close to the calling songs of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Puissant &amp; Boulard" authorityYear="2000" box="[247,410,1169,1193]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicadetta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerdaniensis">
<emphasis box="[247,410,1169,1193]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">C. cerdaniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.Therefore, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sueur &amp; Puissant" authorityYear="2007" box="[541,681,1169,1193]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicadetta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cantilatrix">
<emphasis box="[541,681,1169,1193]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">C. cantilatrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is avalid species (
<bibRefCitation author="HERTACH, T." box="[875,1030,1169,1193]" pageId="23" pageNumber="252" pagination="25 - 40" refId="ref17141" refString="HERTACH, T. 2011. Spectacular song pattern from the Sicilian Mountains: The new cicada species Cicadetta anapaistica sp. n. (Hemiptera: Cicadidae). Zootaxa 2771: 25 - 40." type="journal article" year="2011">Hertach, 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1074,913,1545]" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">
It is possible that 
<bibRefCitation author="BREMI, H." box="[414,557,1201,1225]" pageId="23" pageNumber="252" pagination="325 - 339" refId="ref15650" refString="BREMI, H. 1849. Uebersicht der schweizerischen Rhynchoten. Mittheilungen der Naturforschenden Gesellschaft in Zurich 34: 325 - 339." type="journal article" year="1849">Bremi (1849)</bibRefCitation>
and his German colleague Siebold already knew about this species. There is an older reference to a population in Diegten (BL, Jura Mountains; 
<bibRefCitation author="ARTMANN, G." box="[275,435,1265,1289]" pageId="23" pageNumber="252" pagination="190 - 192" refId="ref15340" refString="ARTMANN, G. 1987. Die fremdsprachige Bergzikade (Cicadetta montana peregrina). Mit - teilungen der Entomologischen Gesellschaft Basel 37 (4): 190 - 192." type="journal article" year="1987">Artmann, 1987</bibRefCitation>
) where the species is still present and frequent. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sueur &amp; Puissant" authorityYear="2007" box="[934,1073,1265,1289]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicadetta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cantilatrix">
<emphasis box="[934,1073,1265,1289]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">C. cantilatrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not rare in 
<collectingCountry box="[298,423,1297,1321]" name="Switzerland" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
and it is surprising that it was not detected earlier (
<bibRefCitation author="HERTACH, T." pageId="23" pageNumber="252" pagination="37 - 61" refId="ref17011" refString="HERTACH, T. 2007. Three species instead of only one: Distribution and ecology of the Cicadetta montana species complex (Hemiptera: Cicadoidea) in Switzerland. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft 80: 37 - 61." type="journal article" year="2007">Hertach, 2007</bibRefCitation>
). It is well distributed in the 
<collectingRegion box="[501,545,1329,1353]" country="Switzerland" name="Jura" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">Jura</collectingRegion>
Mountains including the Randen massif in the east and entering to the eastern part of the hilly Swiss Plateau. We have found 17 local populations solely in the 
<collectingRegion box="[415,604,1393,1417]" country="Switzerland" name="Aargau" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">Canton of Aargau</collectingRegion>
, some of them abundant. It also occurs quite regularly in the lower 
<collectingRegion box="[382,446,1425,1449]" country="Switzerland" name="Valais" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">Valais</collectingRegion>
and in the Chablais (VD). The main distribution is split into two big disjunct metapopulations in 
<collectingCountry box="[567,692,1457,1481]" name="Switzerland" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[712,757,1457,1481]" country="Switzerland" name="Jura" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">Jura</collectingRegion>
and Chablais/ 
<collectingRegion box="[923,990,1457,1481]" country="Switzerland" name="Valais" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">Valais</collectingRegion>
). Additionally,there are three supposedly isolated local populations: Immenberg(TG, discovered by Keist), Uetliberg(ZH, discovered by Rey) and Epesses (VD).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="252" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1067,1569,1657]" box="[151,394,1569,1592]" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">ECOLOGY AND THREAT</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1067,1569,1657]" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sueur &amp; Puissant" authorityYear="2007" box="[227,375,1601,1625]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicadetta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cantilatrix">
<emphasis box="[227,375,1601,1625]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">C. cantilatrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is specialized on sparse Scots Pine forests with a grass-rich understorey on marl (= 
<emphasis box="[415,579,1633,1657]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="252">Molinio-Pinion</emphasis>
,see Delarze &amp;Gonseth, 2008) and variable
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="253" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="24.[173,1022,874,926]" pageId="24" pageNumber="253">
FIG.9 Distribution map of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sueur &amp; Puissant" authorityYear="2007" box="[370,570,904,926]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicadetta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="253" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cantilatrix">
<emphasis box="[370,570,904,926]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="253">Cicadetta cantilatrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
including solely acoustically checked records.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[136,1059,964,1340]" pageId="24" pageNumber="253">
edges of the forest along extensively used semidry meadows normally with Upright Brome (
<emphasis box="[226,393,997,1020]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="253">Bromus erectus</emphasis>
)(= 
<emphasis box="[443,590,996,1020]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="253">Mesobromion</emphasis>
,see Delarze &amp;Gonseth, 2008) in the 
<collectingRegion box="[1001,1045,997,1020]" country="Switzerland" name="Jura" pageId="24" pageNumber="253">Jura</collectingRegion>
Mountains and in the Chablais and on sparse woods with Downy Oak (
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="24" pageNumber="253" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pubescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="253">Quercus pubescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
)in the 
<collectingRegion box="[322,387,1060,1084]" country="Switzerland" name="Valais" pageId="24" pageNumber="253">Valais</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="HERTACH, T." box="[402,560,1060,1084]" pageId="24" pageNumber="253" pagination="37 - 61" refId="ref17011" refString="HERTACH, T. 2007. Three species instead of only one: Distribution and ecology of the Cicadetta montana species complex (Hemiptera: Cicadoidea) in Switzerland. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft 80: 37 - 61." type="journal article" year="2007">Hertach, 2007</bibRefCitation>
). In contrast to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1772" box="[733,858,1061,1084]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicadetta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="253" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis box="[733,858,1061,1084]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="253">C. montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
,it scarcely occurs on rocky cliffs and ridges. It is a stenoecious species whose abundance is often correlated with nature conservation measures and traditional land use.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[136,1059,964,1340]" pageId="24" pageNumber="253">
Beyond 
<collectingCountry box="[301,431,1156,1180]" name="Switzerland" pageId="24" pageNumber="253">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
, the distribution area is large, but acomparable abundance is not known. It therefore seems that the Swiss responsibility for its conservation is high. As in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1772" box="[258,382,1221,1244]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicadetta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="253" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis box="[258,382,1221,1244]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="253">C. montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[389,447,1221,1244]" pageId="24" pageNumber="253" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, it benefits from recent improvements of suitable habitats (
<bibRefCitation author="HERTACH, T." box="[143,300,1252,1276]" pageId="24" pageNumber="253" pagination="37 - 61" refId="ref17011" refString="HERTACH, T. 2007. Three species instead of only one: Distribution and ecology of the Cicadetta montana species complex (Hemiptera: Cicadoidea) in Switzerland. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft 80: 37 - 61." type="journal article" year="2007">Hertach, 2007</bibRefCitation>
). The very active role of cantonal authorities in thinning out pine forests might create an important positive factor for the current frequency in the Cantons of 
<collectingRegion box="[136,214,1316,1340]" country="Switzerland" name="Aargau" pageId="24" pageNumber="253">Aargau</collectingRegion>
and Basel-Land.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
